The paper proposes a model for machine reading comprehension, which is a subfield of natural language processing. The model specifically addresses the task of predicting whether a question is unanswerable, which falls under the category of question answering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes topics related to natural language processing. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these sub-categories also cover topics related to machine learning and natural language processing.
